OL,3,CInvest in childhood 'or risk losing a
OL,4,Cgeneration to poor mental health'
OL,6,FSome recommendations "require targeted
OL,7,Fspending", the report said, while
OL,8,F"others require a shift in the way
OL,9,Fpolicies are created, and will not
OL,10,Fcreate additional costs but rather use
OL,11,Fexisting resources more effectively".
OL,13,FIt added: "All of these actions are
OL,14,Ffar less costly than allowing young
OL,15,Fpeople's needs to escalate until they
OL,16,Frequire specialist care or face
OL,17,Ffinancial adversity and lifelong
OL,18,Fdisadvantage."
