OL,3,CInvest in childhood 'or risk losing a
OL,4,Cgeneration to poor mental health'
OL,6,F"From boosting health visiting and
OL,7,Fparenting programmes, to helping
OL,8,Fschools become mentally healthier
OL,9,Fplaces to learn, it can affect a sea
OL,10,Fchange in the next generation's mental
OL,11,Fhealth. Investing in childhood is
OL,12,Fworth every penny."
OL,14,FA Department of Health and Social Care
OL,15,Fspokesperson said: "Every child should
OL,16,Fhave access to support, which is why
OL,17,Fwe are working to ensure children
OL,18,Freceive high quality mental health
OL,19,Fsupport close to home.
